        2 => /* 24 offsets for thickness 2 */,
        _ => &[],
    };

    for (dx, dy) in offsets {
        let px = (x as i16 + dx).max(0) as u16;
        let py = (y as i16 + dy).max(0) as u16;
        // Render outline character (same char or block) at offset
        // Skip if would overlap main text position
    }
}
```

### Outline Characters:
- Use same character as text for true stroke effect
- Or use block character '█' for solid outline

### Z-Order:
1. Render outline first (all 8/24 positions)
2. Render main text on top

## Files
crates/ftui-extras/src/text_effects.rs

## Unit Tests (REQUIRED)
- test_outline_8_neighbors: thickness=1 fills 8 adjacent cells
- test_outline_24_neighbors: thickness=2 fills 24 cells
- test_outline_solid_continuous: No gaps in solid style
- test_outline_dashed_alternates: Gaps at dash_len intervals
- test_outline_double_two_rings: Two concentric outlines
- test_outline_gradient_animates: Colors cycle over time
- test_outline_under_text: Main text visible on top
- test_outline_at_edge: No panic at terminal bounds

## Visual Tests
- Snapshot 'OUTLINE' with solid white outline, thickness=1
- Snapshot with gradient outline at t=0 and t=0.5
- Snapshot Double style showing two-line effect

## Acceptance Criteria
- Deliver the behavior implied by the title: Text Effects: Border/Outline Effects
- Alien Artifact: define invariants + failure modes; if heuristics exist, specify an explainable decision rule (evidence ledger / Bayes factors where applicable)
- Extreme Optimization: baseline -> profile -> opportunity matrix; for each perf change include an isomorphism proof + golden output checksums
- Unit tests: happy path + edge cases + regression fixtures; add property tests for core invariants where applicable
- E2E: scripts with verbose JSONL logging (env, capabilities, timings, seed, checksums) + deterministic mode
